\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy governs real-time detection and operational response:
 collecting monitoring data,
 classifying events,
 generating work orders for actionable conditions,
 and routing threshold breaches to the capacity and availability investigation process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The threshold values that this policy implements are defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
;
 proactive planning,
 baselining,
 and threshold definition are governed there.
 This policy governs operational performance monitoring and is distinct from the security event logging governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Audit Logging and Monitoring Policy);
 these are separate data streams,
 and the boundary between them is maintained intentionally.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Monitoring Scope and Configuration Ownership
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Department shall maintain real-time monitoring coverage across all IT services,
 infrastructure,
 endpoints,
 and applications within the scope defined in Section 2.
 In-scope data collection includes availability and ping checks,
 performance metrics,
 flow data,
 syslog and event logs,
 and SNMP polling.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Network Administrator shall maintain monitoring configurations for all network equipment within scope.
 The Systems Administrator shall maintain the monitoring collection infrastructure and all server-side monitoring configurations.
 The Assistant IT Director shall verify that both configuration sets are current,
 functional,
 and producing data sufficient to support event classification under this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Tool configurations,
 procedures,
 and monitoring runbooks shall be maintained in the Knowledge Base under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Monitoring data collected under this policy shall be provided to the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Service Level Management and Metrics Reporting) reporting process as an input to monthly performance summary reports.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Event Taxonomy
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall ensure that all events generated by the monitoring function are classified under the following four-tier taxonomy,
 regardless of monitoring stream.
 A single taxonomy governs all in-scope monitoring data types.
 Severity levels referenced below correspond to the severity classification framework defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Service Catalog and SLA Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Informational
\series default
:
 System behavior is within normal parameters.
 No action is required.
 Events at this tier shall be logged for baseline and trending purposes.
 No work order is generated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Warning
\series default
:
 System behavior is approaching a defined threshold.
 No action is required.
 Events at this tier shall be logged.
 The Assistant IT Director shall maintain awareness of Warning-tier events as part of the threshold review obligations established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 No work order is generated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Alert
\series default
:
 A defined threshold has been breached and action is required.
 A work order shall be generated in the 
\series bold
System of Engagement
\series default
 at Urgent or High severity,
 determined by the scope of impact at the time of the event.
 Alert-tier events initiate the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
